                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-086",
                                                 "english":  "Outside in the garden, over the dinner tables, the three objects Scrimgeour had given them were passed from hand to hand."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-087",
                                                 "english":  "Everyone exclaimed over the Deluminator and The Tales of Beedle the Bard and lamented the fact that Scrimgeour had refused to pass on the sword, but none of them could offer any suggestion as to why Dumbledore would have left Harry an old Snitch."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-088",
                                                 "english":  "As Mr."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-089",
                                                 "english":  "Weasley examined the Deluminator for the third or fourth time, Mrs."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-090",
                                                 "english":  "Weasley said tentatively, “Harry, dear, everyone’s awfully hungry, we didn’t like to start without you."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-091",
                                                 "english":  "."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-092",
                                                 "english":  "."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-093",
                                                 "english":  "."
                                             },
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-094",
                                                 "english":  "Shall I serve dinner now?”"
                                             }
                                         ]
                       },
                       {
                           "id":  "p-038",
                           "sentences":  [
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-095",
                                                 "english":  "They all ate rather hurriedly and then, after a hasty chorus of “Happy Birthday” and much gulping of cake, the party broke up."
                                             }
                                         ]
                       },
                       {
                           "id":  "p-039",
                           "sentences":  [
                                             {
                                                 "id":  "s-096",
                                                 "english":  "Hagrid, who was invited to the wedding the following day, but was far too bulky to sleep in the overstretched Burrow, left to set up a tent for himself in a neighboring field."
                                             }
                                         ]
                       }
                   ],
    "translations":  {
                         "s-086":  "庭の食卓では、スクリムジョールが渡した三つの品が皆の手に渡った。",
                         "s-087":  "皆は灯消しライターと『吟遊詩人ビードルの物語』に驚き、剣が渡されなかったことを惜しんだが、なぜ古いスニッチをハリーに残したのかは誰にも分からなかった。",
                         "s-088":  "ウィーズリー氏が",
                         "s-089":  "三度も四度も灯消しライターを調べていると、ウィーズリー夫人がためらいがちに言った。",
                         "s-090":  "「ハリー、みんなお腹をすかせているの。あなた抜きで始めたくなくて。",
                         "s-091":  "……",
                         "s-092":  "……",
                         "s-093":  "……",
                         "s-094":  "もう夕食にしていいかしら？」",
                         "s-095":  "皆は急いで食べ、「ハッピー・バースデー」を慌ただしく歌い、ケーキを飲み込むように食べると、会はお開きになった。",
                         "s-096":  "翌日の結婚式に招かれていたハグリッドは、手狭な隠れ穴には泊まれず、近くの野原に自分のテントを張りに出ていった。"
                     }
